technical_skills: The Linux Systems Engineer is responsible for the support and implementation of Linux and other IT Infrastructure services across the enterprise. This position is also responsible for day to day operation and maintenance of critical business systems. The Linux Systems Engineer successfully executes and tests scheduled monthly maintenance plans to include, system jobs, backups, patch deployment, system changes, server automation, securing of various Linux platforms. - Essential Functions - Install and configure new servers with operating systems, applications, tools, and patches. - Monitor network and systems health, responding appropriately to network alerts and events. - Install firmware, software, and operating system patches and updates. - Audit backups, replication, network activity, disk space, and uptime. - Assist in maintaining network data centers, wiring closets, cabling, servers, consoles, switches, routers, hubs, etc. - Respond quickly to outages as reported via ticketing systems, email and telephone. - Grant / revoke access to various system resources. - Perform Active Directory user administration as it relates to Linux. - Adhere to Change Control, Change Log, and Downtime Log procedures for all services. - Appropriately escalate issues to proper team members. Required Skills - Bachelor`s degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience. - 10+ years IT experience. - Must have an excellent working knowledge of Red Hat Enterprise Release 6/7, CentOS, and Ubuntu - Must have competency with Amazon Web Services - Must have competency with Chef/DevOps. - Must have competency with administration of both Windows and Linux - Must have competency with Windows 2008, 2012, Active Directory - Must be physically able to lift and move computers, monitors, and related equipment with weights in the 10 to 80 pound range. - Must have an excellent working knowledge of, NFS, LDAP, Sendmail, HTTP, SSH, DNS, Samba, DHCP, iptables, Centrify Suite, Server  Hardening, BASH, PERL, Korn, OpenSSH - Must have an excellent working knowledge of Nagios, MySQL - Must have competency with Atlassian products (JIRA) - Ability to quickly diagnose network problems and implement solutions to restore functionality. - Must be accurate and prompt in the details of the job. - Must have good communication skills and have the ability to work with others
